
Create virtual env:
>> python3 -m venv venv

Activate virtual env:
>> source <env_name>/bin/activate

(NB: to deactivate virtual env: deactivate)

Install requirements:
>> cd sbMACROv2.0
>> pip install -r requirements.txt

--- In case of issues with mysqlclient ---
(https://stackoverflow.com/a/12814672/8379443)
>> sudo apt-get install libmysqlclient-dev python-dev
...then try again


Run the application:
>> python sbmacro.py
(Output: Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000/)

Open http://127.0.0.1:5000/ or localhost:5000 in a browser

Done!

==== GIT ====
Install git:
>> sudo apt install git

Initialize the folder:
>> git init

